meta_title: CHAMPION 06552 X1 #1 SCREW EXTRACTOR & XL5H 5/64 LEFT HAND JOBBER DRIL
short_description: Matching combination left hand industrial steel screw extractor and high speed steel twist drill Made in the USA Screw extractor spiral flute design Brute Platinum twist drill avoids needing pilot hole, 135 degree split point Use left hand twist drills in left hand rotation machinery
summary: Champion Cutting Tool ipac system provides you with professional grade cutting tool combinations of industrial steel screw extractor and Brute Platinum left hand high speed steel twist drill designed for electrical, plumbing, mechanical contracting, welding, machine shop and home maintenance. Brute Platinum XL5LH jobber length twist drills outperform standard "drill bits". You will get faster hole penetration and more holes per drill. Each twist drill is provided with a unique combination of premium high speed steel, geometries and NOMO (Nitride on Margin Only) surface treatment. This combination of treatment inables Brute Platinum twist drills to penetrate multiple 300 and 400 series stainless steel, austenitic stainless steel, mild and hardened titanium steel alloys, carbon steel and softer steel materials like copper alloys. Nitriding is the best substitute for cobalt drills and still has flexibility to avoid shattering. With the precision ground 135 degree split point tip there is no need to predrill pilot holes. Brute Platinum left hand twist drills will bit right into the material avoiding the walking effect in common 118 degree twist drills. Designed for use in left hand rotation multiple spindle, gear driven drilling heads, scew machine operations, lathes and any machinery with a left hand rotation. Left hand twist drills are also commonly used for drilling out broken or frozen bolts. The tapered web geometry in each twist drill provides faster penetration of the material. Our matching X1 industrial steel left hand, spiral flute, screw extractors are designed to remove broken screws, studs, bolts, or pipe fittings. The left hand rotation of the tapered flutes forces out almost any right hand threaded part. Recommended to be used with penetrating oil when removing rusty or corroded parts.
